ation was \"not an invasion,\" \"not an extended military operation,\" and forces were \"on the ground for about two hours when they went to capture Maduro\"\n- From DX-2 (Department of War transcript): Operation was \"grabbing an indicted individual wanted by American justice in support of law enforcement\"\n\nThe evidence demonstrates that the objective was fundamentally a capture and extraction operation - a head of state capture without territorial occupation. While PX-1 has language about Maduro being \"now out of power\" and U.S. oversight of the transition, the core military operation was a special operations raid to capture Maduro, returning him for prosecution in the United States.\n\nThe proposition specifically excludes \"special operations raids without territorial objectives\" and \"capture of a head of state without territorial occupation.\" Although Maduro was removed from power, the record indicates this was the result of his capture and removal from Venezuela, not through U.S. ground forces maintaining control over territory or a government-institutional structure after the capture.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_89dda691574b4fa789c57bd4","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted record shows this was a special operations raid to capture Maduro (head of state) without territorial occupation, which the proposition explicitly excludes from qualifying as 'seizing or holding territory, removing the sitting government, or establishing operational control.'\"}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3-coder-plus","usage":{"input":16492,"output":602,"cacheRead":16128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33222,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782783133122,"responseId":"gen-1782783133-dDoOU5NNrohiuFN4rcKh"}}
